    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "REVIEW",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "SAUCERS IN THE NEWS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "MAYAGUEZ, PUERTO RICO, Oct. 3, 1952—",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "Strange objects were sighted by two per-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "sons in Mayaguez on Oct. 3. They were",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "cruising East and were red in color. It was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "about 10:30 p.m. when they were sighted.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "NORWAY AND SWEDEN, Oct. 13, 1952—",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "During October the Norwegian Govern-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "ment stated that a strange object resemb-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "ling a saucer landed on Norwegian soil.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "German experts are claiming that the de-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "vices are of Russian origin, and the des-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "cription given by Norway fits the descrip-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "tion given by German experts. Stockholm,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "Sweden, has also been sighting strange",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "objects.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "MELBOURNE, AUSTRALIA, Sept. 13, 1952",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "—A young woman sighted a noiseless",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "green ball flying too fast to be a plane or a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "meteor. She said it smelled like a rotten",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "egg.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "STUTTGART, GERMANY, Nov. 1, 1952—",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "At the recent meeting of the third Inter-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "national Astronomical Congress in Ger-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "many where 200 scientists from 12 coun-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "tries gathered they stated that saucers are",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "not from Mars or any other planet. They",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "said they are merely optical and atmos-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "pheric illusions.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "JAMAICA, NEW YORK—A terrific air",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "panic took place over a small area of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "Long Island N.Y. which broke windows,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "cracked sidewalks and caused general",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "panic. There were no planes around or",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "scheduled at that time, Oct. 1952.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, NEW YORK,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "Oct. 16, 1952—A blue flame flashed over",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "International Airport at 7:33 p.m. It was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "a fiery ball-like object. Hayden Planetar-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "ium official stated it may have been the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "tail of a meteor.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "TOWNSHIP, YORK, ENGLAND, Sept. 20,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "1952—During exercise \"Mainbrace\" RAF",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "pilots sighted a white object at 15,000",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "feet. The object was silver in color and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "circular. It maintained a slow forward",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "speed before beginning to descend, swing-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "ing like a pendulum. It followed the air-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "craft, revolved on its own axis at times,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "text": "and then took off.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "text": "WASHINGTON, D.C., Oct. 16, 1952—The",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 61,
      "text": "Navy announced that it launched rockets",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 62,
      "text": "from giant balloons, high above the North",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 63,
      "text": "Geomagnetic Pole, and sent them to alti-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 64,
      "text": "tudes of about 40 miles. The balloons were",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 65,
      "text": "as tall as a 10-story building.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 66,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 67,
      "text": "PARIS, FRANCE, Oct. 7, 1952—A flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 68,
      "text": "saucer was sighted over Southern France",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 69,
      "text": "by two Air France pilots.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 70,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 71,
      "text": "WESTERN KOREA FRONT, Oct. 29, 1952",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 72,
      "text": "—U.S. troops saw a half-dozen mysterious",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 73,
      "text": "spark-throwing \"cartwheels\" over the wes-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 74,
      "text": "tern front of Korea. They were as the eye",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 75,
      "text": "sees, 18 inches in diameter, moving in a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 76,
      "text": "15-foot circle.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 77,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 78,
      "text": "GAILLAC, SOUTH OF FRANCE, Oct. 29,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 79,
      "text": "1952—For the second time in two weeks,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 80,
      "text": "20 townspeople of Gaillac saw a series of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 81,
      "text": "white circular objects, slightly swollen at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 82,
      "text": "the center, spinning across the sky. They",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 83,
      "text": "were flying in formation of two and were",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 84,
      "text": "grouped around something that looked",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 85,
      "text": "like a giant flying cigar. As the objects",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 86,
      "text": "passed overhead they let fall a sort of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 87,
      "text": "string of bright white threads, which set-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 88,
      "text": "tled gently on trees and telephone lines.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 89,
      "text": "When the people tried to pick them up,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 90,
      "text": "they melted like ice. A police officer who",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 91,
      "text": "picked up some of the threads said: \"It",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 92,
      "text": "looked like glass wool and it melted away",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 93,
      "text": "almost as soon as it was touched.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 94,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 95,
      "text": "OLORON, FRANCE, Oct. 17, 1952—About",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 96,
      "text": "a dozen people, including a schoolmaster,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 97,
      "text": "saw flying saucers surrounding a long cigar",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 98,
      "text": "like object flying through a clear sky at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 99,
      "text": "about 6,000 feet.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 100,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 101,
      "text": "NEW ZEALAND—The clippings and stor-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 102,
      "text": "ies from New Zealand are swamping our",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 103,
      "text": "office and are so numerous that we must",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 104,
      "text": "devote a whole page to them in our April",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 105,
      "text": "issue.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 106,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 107,
      "text": "For more detailed information on any",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 108,
      "text": "of the above, please write to IFSB.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 109,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 110,
      "text": "Please date your clippings that you send",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 111,
      "text": "to us, and note the source.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    }
  ],
